# Virtual environment
venv/
env/
.venv/
.env/

# Environment variables
.env

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd

# PostgreSQL
*.sql.bak

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```

Place this at the **root of the repo** so it covers the whole project. 

One important note — `.env` is in there which means your database credentials and secret key won't get pushed to GitHub. Make sure you tell your teammates to create their own local `.env` file using the variables you defined earlier. A good practice is to also add a `.env.example` file to the repo with the variable names but no actual values, like:
```
DATABASE_URL=
SECRET_KEY=